<br>
The THought Horror Overfiend fight in The Deep is a pest, not because the mob is horrendously difficult, but because he has a TON of hit points, extremely high melee damage mitigation, and has 2 nasty AoEs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Overfiend's Fury</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is an extremely long lasting Slow and DoT, removable with a Dispel. make dern sure to dispel this after the fight. because it may kill you over time.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Feeblemind</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> make you fizzle like CRAZY! Even at lvl 65 with Spell Casting Masteyr 3, I fizzle a ton of spells. This effect is only removable by Remove Curse spells and I think Radiant Cure.<br>
<br>
What effect does this have on pets? Wlel the Overfiend Fury DoT slowly wears your pet down, it's not TOO bad on lvl61+ pets, but if you try to heal them...fizzle...fizzle..<br>
it also SLOWS your pet.<br>
So what to do?<br>
<br>
Constantly dispel your pet when it's hit by Overfiend's fury!<br>
Even when casting etc, you can type in. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>/pet report health</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to see if the Fury is on the pet. If it is you can use Pumice stones, buyable form vendors to dispel your pet from inventory, because it's a right click it will NOT fizzle!<br>
Also if you have Velious armour quest legs, you can right click re-buff your pet if need. (Mages also have Robe of Burning Rage and a Shield from Sarryn in PoP with pet buff right click).<br>
<br>
This way, even if you may fizzle like hell, and melee's are slowed, your PET won't be! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
